---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import StatsBar from '../components/StatsBar.astro';
import LineageTimeline from '../components/LineageTimeline';
---

<Base
  title="Signal-Driven Development | DDD's Missing Definition of Done"
  description="Three-pass convergence. Gap reports as diagnostic signals. Zero unresolved gaps. A rigorous definition of done for Domain-Driven Design."
  canonicalPath="/"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script
      type="application/ld+json"
      set:html={JSON.stringify({
        '@context': 'https://schema.org',
        '@type': 'Organization',
        name: 'Signal-Driven Development',
        url: 'https://signal-driven-development.vercel.app',
        description:
          'A rigorous, solo-practitioner methodology for Domain-Driven Design with zero unresolved gaps as the definition of done.',
      })}
    />
  </Fragment>

  <Hero />
  <StatsBar />

  <section id="methodology" class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <h2>What is Signal-Driven Development?</h2>
      <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: var(--space-4); line-height: 1.8;">
        SDD is a solo-practitioner methodology for Domain-Driven Design. It introduces
        <strong style="color: var(--text-primary);">gap reports</strong> — structured diagnostic signals
        that measure the completeness and consistency of a domain specification. The definition of done
        is simple: <strong style="color: var(--text-primary);">zero unresolved gaps</strong>.
      </p>
      <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: var(--space-4); line-height: 1.8;">
        A domain specification iterates through passes. Each pass runs a gap report that identifies
        structural, heuristic, language, and decision gaps. The architect resolves each gap. Typical
        trajectory: <strong style="color: var(--text-primary);">18 → 5 → 0</strong> gaps across three
        passes.
      </p>
      <div style="display: flex; gap: var(--space-4); margin-top: var(--space-8); flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <a href="/gap-categories" class="btn btn--secondary">Explore gap categories</a>
        <a href="#lineage" class="btn btn--secondary">See the DDD lineage</a>
        <a href="/get-started" class="btn btn--secondary">Get started</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="lineage" class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Standing on shoulders</h2>
      <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); max-width: 640px; margin-bottom: var(--space-8);">
        SDD builds on two decades of DDD contributions. Every concept has a lineage. Click any node
        to see what SDD inherits.
      </p>
      <LineageTimeline client:visible />
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
